\begin{frame}{Alternative explantions}

\begin{itemize}
	\item[1.] Syntax preplanning / use of syntactic route is non-deterministic
	\item[2.] Preplanning beyond the first noun is not obligated by the production system but more likely for conjoined NPs.
	\item[$\rightarrow$] Fluency pressure requires preplanning of B in \textit{The A and the B moved \dots} if there is not enough time to plan B in parallel to articulation \parencite{all07,griffin2003reversed}.
